Source: flagcx
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: FlagOS Contributors <contact@flagos.io>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               g++ (>= 9),
               make,
               cmake,
               patchelf
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/flagos-ai/FlagCX
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/flagos-ai/FlagCX
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/flagos-ai/FlagCX.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no
X-Build-Environment: This package is designed to be built in backend-specific
 container environments that provide the necessary hardware SDK:
 .
  - NVIDIA backend: Requires CUDA toolkit (>= 12.0) and libnccl-dev
    Built in nvcr.io/nvidia/cuda:12.4.1-devel-ubuntu22.04 container
 .
  - MetaX backend: Requires maca_sdk (from repos.metax-tech.com)
    Built in Ubuntu 22.04 with MetaX APT repository configured
 .
 The Build-Depends listed above are for the Debian packaging tools only.
 Backend-specific dependencies are provided by the container environment.

Package: libflagcx-metax
Build-Profiles: <!pkg.flagcx.nvidia-only>
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: FlagCX communication library for MetaX hardware
 FlagCX is a scalable and adaptive cross-chip communication library.
 It serves as a platform where developers, researchers, and AI engineers
 can collaborate on various projects.
 .
 This package contains the shared library built for MetaX hardware with
 MCCL backend support.

Package: libflagcx-metax-dev
Build-Profiles: <!pkg.flagcx.nvidia-only>
Section: libdevel
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libflagcx-metax (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: FlagCX development files for MetaX hardware
 FlagCX is a scalable and adaptive cross-chip communication library.
 .
 This package contains the header files and development files for
 building applications against libflagcx-metax.

